    "A memoir, <em>Old Friends: Personal Recollections</em>, was published in 1956.": [],
    "Bell's book, <em>Art</em> was highly influential.": [],
    "It went through numerous editions and established the Bloomsbury art-for-art's sake esthetic, \"significant form\" condoning form, independent of content, as most significant aspect of a work of art.": [],
    "As such, Bell could link the art of different periods together through their form, such as works from the renaissance and modern eras.": [],
